VenueAT&T Stadium, Dallas TX

HAVE A CATCH WITH DAK

An enter-to-win contest that gave one lucky fan an all-expenses-paid trip to the Cowboys facility to play catch with Dak Prescott. The campaign combined a talent-driven social launch, in-stadium gameday integration via jumbotron QR codes, and intimate storytelling — connecting a single brand moment across every channel from AT&T Stadium to Instagram.

My Role

  • Led on-site production and activation at AT&T Stadium
  • Coordinated talent content shoot and :60 promo video with Dak Prescott for Instagram & Twitter distribution across athlete, Cowboys, and AT&T accounts
  • Managed in-stadium jumbotron integration and QR-code gameday promotion
  • Oversaw recap video production chronicling the winner's full fan journey
  • Managed client relationship end-to-end from brief to execution

"Best experience ever! Super thankful. Thank you @korbenlondon, @jordan__godwin and the rest of the team!"

— Contest Winner, @cynkilla via Instagram

02 — AT&T 5G
ClientAT&T
Year2021–2022
TypeMulti-Market Experiential / Integrated
MarketsDallas · New York · Los Angeles

AT&T 5G ROADSHOW

A fully integrated, multi-market experiential platform built to drive brand relevance and product education for AT&T's 5G network. The Roadshow unified live activations, gaming influencer partnerships with TimTheTatman and Nadeshot, Twitch livestreams, YouTube content, and earned media into one omnichannel campaign — positioning AT&T as a culturally credible player in gaming and esports.

My Role

  • Supported execution of multi-market activations including tentpole sporting events and high-foot-traffic installations
  • Coordinated influencer integrations with TimTheTatman and Nadeshot across Twitch and YouTube
  • Managed live content and social amplification strategy to extend on-site reach digitally
  • Leveraged partnership rights and co-branded assets across owned, earned, and partner channels

03 — AT&T × LA Clippers
ClientAT&T
Year2025
TypeAI-Driven Fan Experience
VenueIntuit Dome, Inglewood CA

AT&T CONNECTOPIA

The world's first AI-driven, real-time cinematic 8K environment creation platform inside a live sports venue. Built in partnership with the LA Clippers at Intuit Dome, Connectopia invited fans to design personalized digital worlds through 75-inch touchscreen portals — instantly rendered on a massive 54-foot wraparound display and shareable via mobile. A permanent installation running through 2032.

My Role

  • Supported execution of the permanent installation at Intuit Dome as part of the AT&T account team
  • Coordinated across creative, technology, and venue partners to deliver the multi-touchpoint fan experience
  • Managed omnichannel shareability — mobile web app integration enabling fans to take AI-generated content beyond the arena
  • Contributed to partnership strategy with Clippers and Intuit Dome leadership aligned with the venue's fan-first vision

What I Do

RESPONSIBILITIES

Project Leadership

Lead development and execution of medium to large-scale experiential projects from brief through delivery, managing up to three activations simultaneously across account teams and production partners.

Client Management

Own day-to-day client relationships, establishing credibility and anticipating needs before they arise. Serve as primary point of contact, leading calls and presentations with the ability to adapt to any audience.

Budget & Operations

Develop, manage, and reconcile project budgets of $500K–$1.5M, keeping clients informed throughout and ensuring all deliverables are met on time, on budget, and to Wasserman's quality standards.

Workflow Strategy

Strategically plan workflows around deliverables, understanding task interdependencies and prioritizing accordingly. Assign responsibilities and ensure follow-through even under tight deadlines.

Cross-Functional Collaboration

Partner across Wasserman's creative, production, and account teams to ensure flawless project delivery. Move information efficiently to keep all stakeholders aligned and work moving forward.

Problem Solving & Culture

Troubleshoot and creatively problem-solve in real time with production and creative teams. Identify issues before they escalate, stay calm under pressure, and foster a collaborative team environment.
